# Design Harness (Nativz Cortex)

For **full pages, landing flows, marketing UI, or any substantial interface work**, read the vendored skill:

**`.claude/skills/design-harness/SKILL.md`**

Then apply **this repo’s** implementation path:

1. **`.cursor/rules/northstone-app-ui.mdc`** — Shadcn pipeline, Bedrock motion, typography-first doctrine for Cortex
2. **`.claude/skills/bedrock/SKILL.md`** + **`references/design-doctrine.md`** + **`references/single-prompt-playbook.md`**
3. **`docs/conventions.md`** and **`docs/detail-design-patterns.md`** for UI copy, dark theme, and established tokens

**Project precedence:** Where the harness suggests generic stacks (e.g. “neutral grays, not slate/zinc”), **follow Cortex conventions** — this app already standardizes on dark surfaces, accent, and existing Tailwind tokens.

## Quick reference (from harness)

### Before writing JSX
- Lock **font pairing** (display + body) and **delight budget** (about 1 hero moment + 1 optional mid-page; calm elsewhere)
- Typography and spacing before heavy motion

### Implementation habits
- **Shadcn blocks first** for structure (`npx shadcn@latest add <block>`)
- **One visual system** across sections (radius, borders, button weight)
- **Motion is seasoning** — not wallpaper
- **No magnetic hovers** (Magnet / MagnetLines) — hard ban (see `design-doctrine.md`)
- **Verify:** `npm run build` + `npm run lint` after substantive UI

### External layers (optional installs)
- **Impeccable** (impeccable.style), **Emil Kowalski** (emilkowal.ski/skill), **Interface Design** (interface-design.dev), **UI Skills** (ui-skills.com) — borrowed expertise; see full `SKILL.md` for links and when to use each
- **Paper** (paper.design), **Pencil** (pencil.dev) — agent-native design surfaces
- **Variant**, **Mobbin**, **Awwwards**, **Cosmos** — inspiration / taste training (see `SKILL.md`)

